&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse Cardiac Cath Lab&lt;/strong&gt; – Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Basingstoke&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description:&lt;/strong&gt; Due to a recent promotion we are seeking enthusiastic nurses with some post-registration experience to become an integral member of our friendly and committed team at an exciting time as we expand and develop our services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commitment to learn and develop new knowledge and skills in a well-supported environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work in an often fast paced environment, staying calm and focused, ready to respond in emergency situations, working as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion to deliver high quality care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with an experienced and knowledgeable Cardiology Team where you will be encouraged and well supported to learn and expand clinical skills and knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities to attend National Study Days, Conferences and Training delivered face to face and via e-learning platforms to enhance knowledge, skills and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Joining at an exciting time when we are about to expand our service significantly to meet the growing needs of our population.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your life outside HHFT is important and the Trust are happy to consider applications with flexible working patterns that cater to individual requirements; this can be discussed at interview&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are: &lt;/strong&gt;Situated within Cardiology we are a busy Day Case Unit and Cath Lab that provide highly specialist care to our patients including : Coronary Angiography, Percutaneous Coronary Intervention (Pressure Wire &amp; IVUS), Basic and Complex Pacing ~ ICD,CRT &amp; sICD. You will be well supported in all areas of the Cath Lab and be trained to Scrub, Circulate and manage a group of patients through admission to nurse-led discharge. We also provide a 24hr/365 day Emergency PPCI Service which is a very exciting and rewarding part of our work. Once fully trained you will join the on-call rota where a specialist team support our patients admitted straight to the Lab via ED, 999 and Air Ambulance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the trust: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vision at Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is to provide outstanding care for every patient. We serve a population of nearly 600,000 people across Hampshire and West Berkshire as well as some people who access our specialist services from across the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Created in January 2012 the Foundation Trust prioritises the provision of exceptional, compassionate, care delivered by the valued staff working in a culture of collaboration and mutual respect. HHFT employs circa 6,000 people and had a turnover of £382m in 17/18&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Four core values (CARE) Compassion, Accountability, Respect and Encourage. These are in place to support of four clear objectives, provide outstanding care of patients, empowering all members of staff, sustainable growth and innovating for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; #AspringToBeTheBest &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
